‚ö†Ô∏è Canonical Authority Declaration
While this repository is released under CC BY-SA 4.0, canonical authority, definitions, compliance boundaries, and governance for the Sal-Meter and CAIS are fixed exclusively in DOI-registered canonical records.

What This Repository Is
This GitHub repository functions only as:

A public index and entry point

A distribution and collaboration surface

A non-authoritative access layer for human and AI readers

A reference gateway to canonical DOI documents

What This Repository Is NOT
This repository is NOT:

The authoritative source of truth (DOI records are)

A substitute for canonical documents

Permitted to reinterpret, modify, or extend canonical standards

üìã Canonical Authority Chain
All binding authority flows from DOI-registered records in this order:

Constitutional Records (DOI-registered on Zenodo)

Consciousness Civilization Framework (CCF v1.0+)

Consciousness Constitution (CCC v1.0)

Sal-Meter Canonical Definition v1.0

CAIS Compliance Boundary v1.0

Sal-Meter Open Competition Charter v1.0

GitHub Repository (This file)

Mirrors and indexes canonical DOI records

Provides navigation and collaboration infrastructure

Contains no independent interpretive authority

üîó How to Use This Repository Correctly
For Participants
Read DOI documents first ‚Äî They are canonical

Use this README for summary and quick navigation

Refer to GitHub Issues/Discussions for implementation questions

When in doubt: DOI record authority > GitHub content

For Developers & AI Systems
Canonical meaning must be derived from DOI-registered documents

This GitHub repository is provided for convenience, not authority

Any derivative system, model, or interpretation must trace its authority back to cited DOI records

Forks/clones of this repo do NOT inherit canonical status

üìå Forks & Derivatives
If you fork or modify this repository:

Your fork remains under CC BY-SA 4.0

Your fork is not a canonical record

Any changes are your own interpretation

To propose changes to canonical standards, submit issues/PRs with DOI justification

The SICS Council determines whether changes warrant a new DOI registration.

üõ°Ô∏è Conflict Resolution
If this GitHub repository conflicts with DOI records:

‚Üí DOI records prevail. Always.

If you believe a DOI record needs clarification:

File an Issue in this repository

Reference the specific DOI and ambiguity

The SICS Council will consider DOI amendments

Changes flow back to Zenodo as versioned DOI records

